,(66,1,4,'When is a project complete?','4.15.3 Integration Practice Test',1,1,1,'When the budgeted funds are spent','When formal acceptance has been obtained from the customer','When the work is done','When the customer is satisfied','',0,0,0,0,0,2,0,1,1,'2018-01-01 22:11:36.000','')
,(67,1,4,'Given the complex nature of projects, which area of change generally has the highest impact?','4.15.3 Integration Practice Test',1,1,1,'A change in the company that is creating the project','A change in the market for which the work of the project is intended','A change in the team on the project','A change in the project','',0,0,0,0,0,2,0,1,1,'2018-01-01 22:14:43.000','')
,(68,1,4,'As a best practice, who should create the project management plan?','4.15.3 Integration Practice Test',1,1,1,'Project manager alone','Project manager and the project management team','The project manager, the project management team, and the owner of the project','The project owner alone','',0,0,0,0,0,2,0,1,1,'2018-01-01 22:18:18.000','')
,(69,1,4,'You are the project manager on a restaurant POS system project for Hamburger Prince Restaurants. You are fortunate in having the top technical architect in the company on your project. In your monthly meeting with the CEO, you are informed that the architect will be reassigned to a higher priority enterprise reporting system project. You inform the CEO that the resource''s involvement on your project is critical to the project''s success, but the CEO will not reconsider. What is the best action to take next?','4.15.3 Integration Practice Test',1,1,1,'Evaluate the impact of the person''s absence on the project and communicate to senior management','Continue to lobby for the person to be returned to your project','Change the scope of the project to accommodate for the loss of the resource','Continue as the original plan, but without the resource','',0,0,0,0,0,1,0,1,1,'2018-01-01 22:34:04.000','')
,(70,1,4,'The project will be starting the executing process group next week. The project sponsor and project manager have a meeting scheduled with the team and the business units that are impacted by the project. They explain what is expected to occur on the project and how each of the people can help contribute to the success of the project. What is this event called?','4.15.3 Integration Practice Test',1,1,1,'Kickoff meeting to officially start the project','An integral part of the team building effort','Perform quality assurance and validate scope','Project management plan development','',0,0,0,0,0,1,0,1,1,'2018-01-01 22:44:39.000','')
;
INSERT INTO quiz.quiz_ques (ques_id,quiz_id,sect_id,ques_name,ques_ref,status_id,ques_type_id,diff_level_id,option_a,option_b,option_c,option_d,option_e,option_a_valid,option_b_valid,option_c_valid,option_d_valid,option_e_valid,option_radio_val,option_true_or_false,ques_marks,mk_id,mk_date,mk_comment) VALUES 
(71,1,4,'Of the following, which is not an acceptable method of project creation?','4.15.3 Integration Practice Test',1,1,1,'The project manager creates the project charter and has someone with the appropriate authority sign it','Senior management creates the project charter and signs it','The sponsor creates the project charter and signs it','A project charter is taken from a similar project and reused','',0,0,0,0,0,4,0,1,1,'2018-01-01 22:57:43.000','')
,(72,1,4,'During the monitor and control project work process, the project manager is placing a great deal of reliance on expert judgement. Do you think this reliance is well founded?','4.15.3 Integration Practice Test',1,1,1,'No, if expert judgment is so important there wouldn''t be such a market for modeling tools','Not to such an extent, because modeling tools are more effective','Yes, although modeling tools are effective, expert judgment is often more significant and more accurate than those tools','Not to such an extent, because expert judgment functions only as a check against the results of modeling tools','',0,0,0,0,0,3,0,1,1,'2018-01-01 23:04:46.000','')
,(73,1,4,'The project manager and her team have worked diligently to complete the project scope on time and within budget. They are in the process of creating the project files. Of the following, which is the best complete definition of project files?','4.15.3 Integration Practice Test',1,1,1,'Project documents that record what occurred during the project and what changes were approved','Project documents that record what occurred during the project, what changes were approved, and what decisions were made','Project documents that record what occurred during the project, basic project statistics (scope, time, and cost), and what changes were approved','Project documents that record what occurred during the project, what changes were approved, basic project statistics (scope, time, and cost), and what decisions were made','',0,0,0,0,0,2,0,1,1,'2018-01-01 23:23:39.000','')
,(74,1,4,'The team has just completed the work on a project that contracted with a number of vendors. A contract file was created during the procurement process. What items must be contained in this file?','4.15.3 Integration Practice Test',1,1,1,'For each contract, the bidding documentation, the contract, the approved changes, and the formal acceptance','For each contract, the contract, the approved changes, and the formal acceptance','For each contract, the bidding documentation, the amended contract, and the formal acceptance','For each contract, the amended contract and the formal acceptance','',0,0,0,0,0,2,0,1,1,'2018-01-01 23:33:22.000','')
,(75,1,4,'The Internet project is 65% complete, more or less, and has had it challenges. Senior management tells you that the sponsor has some serious concerns about the project. Based on the last status report, which reflected that the project is on track regarding cost, schedule, and scope, you don''t understand the sponsor''s concern. What should you do first?','4.15.3 Integration Practice Test',1,1,1,'Evaluate the schedule and budget to verify the triple constraint health of the project','Ignore senior management because the project is in good shape','Tell senior management that the project is in good shape','Meet with the sponsor about the concerns','',0,0,0,0,0,4,0,1,1,'2018-01-01 23:42:19.000','')
,(76,1,4,'The healthcare project is in the planning stage and the project manager and his team are making decisions about the project management information system (PMIS). In discussing the system they feel will work best, which of the following statements is the project manager most likely to make?','4.15.3 Integration Practice Test',1,1,1,'It is vital that the system accommodates our need to update payroll for the project management team','It is vital that the system accommodates our need to update the chart of accounts for procurement items','It is vital that the system accommodates our need to access functional management records to identify expert judgment candidates','It is vital that the system accommodates our need to send the right information to the right people in a timely and appropriate manner','',0,0,0,0,0,4,0,1,1,'2018-01-01 23:49:46.000','')
,(77,1,4,'The project manager and his team are in the planning stage of the retooling project and they are making assumptions for scheduling and budgeting. Of the following, what is the most likely source for the assumptions they will make?','4.15.3 Integration Practice Test',1,1,1,'Pertinent human resource and procurement records','Lessons learned from prior projects','Resource list and chart of accounts','Expert judgment and functional management unit','',0,0,0,0,0,2,0,1,1,'2018-01-01 23:55:26.000','')
,(78,1,4,'During the monitor and control project work process for the Meaningful Curriculum project, the project manager and his team are considering performance information. Of the following, which best describes what they will do with this information?','4.15.3 Integration Practice Test',1,1,1,'Document and track the information','Collect, measure, and interpret the information','Determine who will have access to the information','All of the answers','',0,0,0,0,0,2,0,1,1,'2018-01-02 00:00:11.000','')
,(79,1,4,'The company is determining which proposed projects it should pursue during a severe economic downturn. Of the following, which is the most likely project it will approve?','4.15.3 Integration Practice Test',1,1,1,'A project that is proposed in response to a technological advance','A project that is proposed in response to a legal requirement','A project that is proposed in response to a business opportunity','A project that is proposed in response to a business problem','',0,0,0,0,0,2,0,1,1,'2018-01-02 00:06:48.000','')
,(80,1,4,'The project manager and his team have just started the perform integrated change control process for a high profile project. They are carefully considering all the inputs to make certain that the process is conducted successfully. Which of the following is not an input to this process','4.15.3 Integration Practice Test',1,1,1,'Work performance reports','Change control meetings','Change requests','The project management plan','',0,0,0,0,0,2,0,1,1,'2018-01-02 00:11:03.000','')
;
INSERT INTO quiz.quiz_ques (ques_id,quiz_id,sect_id,ques_name,ques_ref,status_id,ques_type_id,diff_level_id,option_a,option_b,option_c,option_d,option_e,option_a_valid,option_b_valid,option_c_valid,option_d_valid,option_e_valid,option_radio_val,option_true_or_false,ques_marks,mk_id,mk_date,mk_comment) VALUES 
(81,1,4,'The company is implementing an enterprise reporting system. This system will integrate a number of business units. As a result, it will be very resource-intensive and could cause reprioritization of other projects that it will replace. Which of the following will be of greatest concern to the project manager?','4.15.3 Integration Practice Test',1,1,1,'Whether the new project will impact the schedule for his project','Whether the new project will impact the budget for his project','Whether the new project will impact the business case for his project','Whether the new project will impact the resources for his project','',0,0,0,0,0,3,0,1,1,'2018-01-02 00:23:03.000','')
,(82,1,4,'You are the project manager for a highway construction project. You have just finished integrating the various management plans into a complete document. What process will you perform next?','4.15.3 Integration Practice Test',1,1,1,'Develop project management plan','Perform integrated change control','Direct and manage project work','Develop project charter','',0,0,0,0,0,3,0,1,1,'2018-01-02 00:33:50.000','')
,(83,1,4,'At the weekly infrastructure project staff meeting, the customer informs the project team that, due to a change in market conditions, he must request a significant change to the product that will be created as a result of the project. The project is 85% complete. What should the project manager do in this case?','4.15.3 Integration Practice Test',1,1,1,'Advise the customer that the project is too close to completion to integrate the change','Evaluate the impact the requested change will have on the project and advise the customer of the impact and his options','Ignore the customer in the hope that he will not pursue the request','Create a new project to accommodate the requested change and release the project as-is to the market','',0,0,0,0,0,2,0,1,1,'2018-01-02 01:08:00.000','')
;